.TH "HTMLLINKELEMENT.MEDIA" "3JS" "July 1, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
HTMLLinkElement.media \- HTMLLinkElement: media property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]media\f[B]\f[R] property of the
\f[CR]HTMLLinkElement\f[R] interface is a string representing a list of
one or more media formats to which the resource applies.
.PP
It reflects the \f[CR]media\f[R] attribute of the \f[CR]<link>\f[R]
element.
.SH VALUE
A string.
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
<\f[B]link\f[R]
  id=\(dqel\(dq
  href=\(dqhttps://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap\(at5.3.3/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css\(dq
  rel=\(dqstylesheet\(dq
  media=\(dqscreen and (width >= 600px)\(dq
  crossorigin=\(dqanonymous\(dq />
.EE
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] el = document.getElementById(\(dqel\(dq);
console.log(el.media); \f[I]// Output: \(dqscreen and (width >= 600px)\(dq\f[R]
.EE
